Join us as a WoW Software EngineerThis is an opportunity for a technically minded individual to join us as a Software EngineerYou’ll be designing, testing and implementing software, working across the lifecycle of the systemHone your existing software engineering skills and advance your career in this critical roleWhile this is a remote first role, you'll be expected to go the London office 2 consecutive days a monthWhat you'll doWorking in a permanent feature team, you’ll be developing knowledge of the platform across the disciplines of business, applications, data and infrastructure. You’ll also be liaising with principal engineers, product managers, designers and other key stakeholders to understand how the platform works and how it supports business objectives.You’ll Also BeApplying Agile methods to the development of software in the backlogProducing resilient and long-lived software and acting flexibly to cope with future needsDelivering intentional architecture and formulating emergent design through innovative ideas, experimentation and prototypingDesigning and developing software with a focus on the automation of build, test and deployment activities, using executable patternsThe skills you'll needWe’re looking for someone with strong full stack experience in software design and implementation, including experience in using programming languages to solve complex problems. You’ll need to be capable of complex requirements analysis capture and validation against business and systems requirements.You’ll also need production experience using React, GraphQL, TypeScript, Node.JS, Jest/Vitest, MySQL, serverless functions and NPM.Additionally, You’ll DemonstrateKnowledge of continuous integration and delivery tooling including GitHub actions and TerraformProduction experience with Amazon Web Services, single page and progressive web apps and monorepo architecturesExperience of working to programming best practice, especially around scalability, automation, virtualisation, optimisation, availability and performanceSound collaboration skills with the ability to work with business teams to produce pragmatic solutions that work for the businessExperience of information security policies and practicesStrong stakeholder management skills and communication skills with the ability to communicate complex technical concepts in a simple way
£100k - £130k

