DevOps Engineer.Scotland/Newcastle upon Tyne, UK (Hybrid)APPLY NOWWe are a software Consultancy, who provide highly skilled consultants to support client business needs. Test Driven Solutions have had a successful start, with our consultants working across green/brown field projects using the latest cutting-edge technologies.We work within private and public sectors, including financial services, government, healthcare, education, property, manufacturing, oil & gas, broadcasting and renewable energy organisations. We are continuously growing as a business, with new client wins and an internal project on-going.We have clear values and a family ethos. We are multidisciplinary and multimedia, with regular meetups online and at in-person events. We maintain a strong connection across our teams and there's a great sense of community in the way we work.Headquartered in the city centre of Newcastle, we have a hybrid office to provide collaborative spaces surrounded by plenty of great spots to socialise. We have recently opened a modern office space, located near Edinburgh’s Haymarket station as a base for our Scottish team to collaborate.Working in cross-functional teams with our clients, supporting the delivery of their initiatives.Contributing to design, development and the operations of internal applications.Communicating effectively, internally and externally.Promoting the TDS company values: Passion, Effectiveness, Transparency, Commitment.Advocating best practices in software development, including XP (TDD), agility, DevOps and CI/CD.Growing the company by contributing to our ongoing recruitment efforts.Being a curious technologist with an appetite to develop new skills.Mentoring TDS staff, growing their technical and consultancy skills.Actively participating in internal product and systems development.In addition to the roles and responsibilities outlined above, a successful candidate will have at least 5 years of professional experience working in a cloud technology environment using AWS, with experience building and operating applications within this space. A candidate will have worked with the following technologies:Containerisation and orchestration technologies, such as Docker, Kubernetes and HelmAn infrastructure as code tool, such as: Terraform, CloudFormationAn Configuration as Code tool, such as : AnsibleA DevOps-friendly programming language, such as Python, Golang or JavaScript (Node)An understanding of a cloud provider’s IAM architecture and its security implicationsA monitoring and logging stack, such as CloudWatch, Splunk, Grafana and PrometheusSecrets Management tooling, such as Vault, AWS Secrets ManagerContinuous Delivery pipelines: GitHub Actions, GitLab, Jenkins, TeamCityCompetitive salary25 days holiday + Bank HolidaysRemote work and flexible working hoursContributory pension scheme (Salary sacrifice optional)Development opportunities/Paid certificatesDiscretionary Bonus SchemeBUPA HealthcarePerkbox benefits/discount schemeCity centre office locationMacbook Pro/Window Machine providedSocial company eventsCompany away weekendTo find out more about working at TDS, head to our Careers page.If you are interested in this position, please send your CV to careers@testdrivensolutions.co.ukWant to work with us?Get in touch today.Want to work with us?Want to work with us?Get in touch today. Name First Last Email Location Poland United Kingdom of Great Britain and Northern Ireland Attach a File Message Do Not Fill This Out

